    {
      "id": "bcc7ae0cc4c644aeead58fecfcab60e2f654ec3b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 464,
        "name": "Elena",
        "email": "elena.gryaznova@hpe.com",
        "username": "elena"
      },
      "date": "2019-04-18 16:29:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAndreas,\nCommit message lists 2 tests:\nsanity 208 (LU-12175)\nsanity 133g (LU-12171)\nrecovery-small 107 (LU-12176)\nrecovery-small 134 (LU-11560)\nThese tests can be added to exclude list. Don't you think that this is reasonable? Or is commit message incorrect?\nThanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "3ce35644490eaaeb194e2475faf2ca9ef3cfd95f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-04-18 16:40:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nCommit message lists 4 tests, and I don't think it's great to exclude tests like that.  That is also just hiding the problem.\n\nAlso, investigation of the test failures leads me to think they are not bugs in these tests, some of which don't do much MDS interaction - they are strange issues which look like they may be config problems coming from earlier tests.  (For example, 133g is confused about the 'active' state of the mds1 facet, which it does not change itself.)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "472cd1a9e916504f03c2ecc415339b0eff9b03ab",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 464,
        "name": "Elena",
        "email": "elena.gryaznova@hpe.com",
        "username": "elena"
      },
      "date": "2019-04-18 16:46:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHaving dir stripe count always equal to 2 is hiding the Lustre striped directories problems.\nI.e. the Lustre released feature is not tested well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
