      "date": "2019-04-18 21:14:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Having dir stripe count always equal to 2 is hiding the Lustre\n > striped directories problems.\n > I.e. the Lustre released feature is not tested well.\n\nSure, I agree that this will revert the testing coverage somewhat, but we can't wait to understand the problems and fix them while we have so many other patches failing.\n\nNow that we know there are problems in this area, it is possible to submit additional patches that re-enable this functionality (possibly on a per-test basis via the DIRSTRIPE_INDEX and DIRSTRIPE_COUNT variables) and then run enough iterations of the tests to ensure that they are passing consistently.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "915ace62ed31c1deebd2775e21295cba757388ff",
      "author": {
